cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

The paper focuses on learning scene flow from point clouds, which is a problem commonly studied in computer vision (CV) and robotics (RO). Therefore, cs.CV and cs.RO are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a novel deep neural network, which involves learning hierarchical features and embeddings, indicating that it may fall under the sub-categories of machine learning (LG) and artificial intelligence (AI). Finally, the paper evaluates the network on Lidar scans, which are commonly used in graphics (GR) and robotics (RO) research.
